    'portfolio.skills.label': 'Skills',
    'portfolio.skills.overview': 'Skill overview',
    'portfolio.skills.summary': 'R&D for automation systems: understand the process, design the loop and tools, test limits, and make the result operational.',
    'portfolio.skills.details': '## Core skills\n\n- R&D / product engineering: domain research, constraint discovery, architecture, prototyping, field validation, release discipline, and turning unclear tasks into operational systems.\n- Loop automation and tooling: Agent Portal, MCP/WebMCP, context engineering, RAG/GraphRAG-style retrieval, project graphs, explicit planning/execution/eval stages, multi-agent orchestration, model/resource routing, tool contracts, structured execution state, retry/replan, guardrails, observability, browser evidence, and audit gates.\n- Full-stack / platform: JavaScript, Node.js, Web/PWA, Web Components, API services, PostgreSQL, WebSocket runtime sync, PM2/nginx operations, deployment scripts, SSH/WebSocket tunnels, and integration across frontend/backend/runtime/ops stacks including Python when needed.\n- Product UI: admin panels, dashboards, editors, graph interfaces, media tools, design systems, provider metadata, component contracts, responsive tool surfaces, and workflows that put prototypes into daily use.\n- End-to-end productization: production setup, team and contractor coordination, training, field logistics, complex packaging, export documentation, international delivery, and practical handoff.\n- Backend/ops and messaging: lifecycle messaging, opt-in SMS scenarios, campaign orchestration, audience segmentation, analytics, internal roles, GSM modem pools, serial/AT-command control, SMS inbox/USSD operations, and repeatable business workflows.\n- Media and hardware: 360 media, photogrammetry, artistic 3D visualization, controlled light, controlled motion, STM32/ESP32 experiments, field capture workflows, physical prototypes, early production, and process automation for real environments.',
    'portfolio.skill.rnd.details': '## R&D / product engineering\n\n- Research unclear domains, find real constraints, separate assumptions from field evidence, and define the smallest useful prototype.\n- Design product and technical architecture around the actual workflow, not around a preferred stack.\n- Move from prototype to operational process: validation, production setup, team scaling and training, packaging and export documentation, international delivery, release gates, and practical handoff.\n- Work across software, AI tooling, media workflows, backend/ops, and physical systems when the task needs it.',
    'portfolio.skill.agenticAi.details': '## Loop automation / MCP-WebMCP tooling\n\n- Design automation as explicit loops: context, planning, execution, and eval stages with defined transitions and completion criteria.\n- Build reusable MCP/WebMCP tools for project graphs, RAG/GraphRAG-style retrieval, browser/context/terminal control, model/resource routing, and multi-agent orchestration.\n- Engineer retry/replan, structured execution state, guardrails, observability, browser evidence, and audit gates into reliable applied workflows.\n- Use agent-assisted development as an internal engineering workflow for research, prototyping, and verifiable implementation.',
    'portfolio.skill.productUi.details': '## Product interfaces\n\n- Build product portals, admin panels, dashboards, editors, graph tools, media tools, and operational interfaces for repeated use.\n- Use Web/PWA, Web Components, provider metadata, reusable UI contracts, responsive layouts, and browser-visible evidence as part of the engineering process.\n- Design interfaces for scanning, comparison, repeated action, review loops, and practical team workflows rather than decorative presentation.',
    'portfolio.skill.hardwareCapture.details': '## Hardware / process automation\n\n- Design and build physical prototypes, controlled-motion systems, capture rigs, lighting setups, and specialized equipment for very small and large objects.\n- After MEGAVISOR, began developing equipment-control software myself in JavaScript/Espruino; extended the line through Wi-Fi/browser control for turntables, camera motion, photogrammetry, 360 media, museum-grade scanning, and automated bottle-catalog photography.\n- Produce artistic 3D visualization of digitized objects — including the full Hermitage netsuke and Kunstkamera bronze collections — and organize the 3D pipeline across photographers, retouchers, visualizers, training, retopology, and color calibration.\n- Treat hardware as a capability in the R&D portfolio: useful when the project needs physical process automation, not as the only career focus.',
    'portfolio.pdf.headerTitle': 'R&D engineer | process-automation systems and platforms',
    'portfolio.pdf.summaryTitle': 'Professional summary',
    'portfolio.pdf.summaryDetails': 'R&D engineer with 15+ years across product platforms, media systems, hardware, and process automation.\n\nI design and develop automation loops for complex processes and systems across domains at the intersection of software, media, and hardware. Using loop engineering, I define context, planning, execution, and evals with explicit transitions and completion criteria, and use RAG/GraphRAG-style retrieval for working context.\n\nCollaboration format: I work remotely — individually as a hands-on lead or senior individual contributor, or by integrating the [RND-PRO team](https://rnd-pro.com/workflow/en/) into the client project for broader-scope work.',
    'portfolio.pdf.impactTitle': 'Selected impact',
    'portfolio.pdf.impactDetails': '## Selected impact\n\n- Loop automation tooling: built reusable MCP/WebMCP tools for context retrieval, planning, execution, evals, resource-aware orchestration, guardrails, observability, and verifiable results.\n- Museum high-detail 3D scanning: developed OBJET.art / ArtClub technology and equipment used at the State Hermitage, Kunstkamera, and other museums; helped train and scale the 3D team.\n- Hardware products: created open-source PhotoPizza and commercial ComplexScan/AUTOBOX; coordinated prototypes, contractor/small-batch fabrication, testing, protective packaging, export documents, and international delivery.\n- MEGAVISOR / Gate9: developed automated photo-360 technology and equipment for warehouses and stores, coordinated 3D photographers and retouchers, and contributed to player functionality.',
    'portfolio.pdf.expertiseTitle': 'Core expertise',
    'portfolio.pdf.expertiseDetails': '## Core expertise\n\n- Loop automation and MCP/WebMCP engineering: MCP/WebMCP, context engineering, RAG/GraphRAG, planning, execution, evals, explicit transitions and completion criteria, retry/replan, guardrails, observability, model/resource routing, multi-agent orchestration, and audit gates.\n- Full-stack: JavaScript/Node.js, Web/PWA/Web Components, APIs/PostgreSQL/WebSockets, PM2/nginx, tunnels and deployment; digital presence and content operations automation.\n- Cross-cutting R&D and technical leadership: research, architecture, prototypes, field validation, explicit ownership, written context, review gates, repeatable verification, and team/contractor coordination.\n- Hardware and process automation: JavaScript/Espruino, GSM modems, serial/AT commands, photogrammetry, controlled light/motion, physical prototypes, and field operation.',
